  <result aggregation-status="0" type="2">
   <title>
    <narrative xml:lang="EN">Results achieved</narrative>
    <narrative xml:lang="SV">Uppn&#xE5;dda resultat</narrative>
   </title>
   <description>
    <narrative xml:lang="EN">In November 2012, the African Risk Capacity (ARC) was established by treaty as a Specialised Agency of the African Union (AU). Sweden has supported the Agency since the onset, providing unearmarked funding with the latest contribution closing in June 2017. The ARC has come a far way since its establishment. It has developed or is in the process of completing the development of additional insurance products to cover hazards beyond drought, including tropical cyclones, flooding and outbreaks and epidemics. Although it has been hampered by a number of challenges, especially in terms of increasing its risk pool at the pace planned (its core business) it has stayed on track in the other areas of its work. There has also been a significant development in the level of understanding and incountry capacities on understanding the concepts of risk transfer, risk management and sovereign weather Insurance. Experience in implementing the ARC mechanism has demonstrated the need to link the technical and political bridge regarding insurance and the role it plays in supporting resilience.</narrative>
   </description>
